WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.780
Chapters 5 and 6 of the Gospel of Mark.

00:05.420 --> 00:11.260
This is a LibriVox recording. All LibriVox recordings are in the public domain.

00:11.820 --> 00:19.100
For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibriVox.org.

00:19.640 --> 00:22.360
Recording by Simon Wainwright.

00:23.520 --> 00:26.680
The Gospel of Mark. Chapter 5.

00:27.480 --> 00:35.080
And they came over onto the other side of the sea, into the country of the Gadarenes.

00:35.460 --> 00:41.800
And when he was come out of the ship, immediately there met him, out of the tombs,

00:42.160 --> 00:50.700
a man with an unclean spirit, who had his dwelling among the tombs, and no man could bind him.

00:50.700 --> 00:59.420
No, not with chains, because that he had been often bound with fetters and chains,

00:59.900 --> 01:06.920
and the chains had been plucked asunder by him, and the fetters broken into pieces,

01:07.580 --> 01:10.520
neither could any man tame him.

01:11.600 --> 01:22.240
And always, night and day, he was in the mountains and in the tombs, crying and cutting himself with stones.

01:22.680 --> 01:30.580
But when he saw Jesus afar off, he ran and worshipped him, and cried with a loud voice,

01:30.880 --> 01:37.680
and said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus, thou son of the Most High God?

01:37.680 --> 01:42.860
I adjure thee, by God, that thou torment me not.

01:43.880 --> 01:50.120
For he said unto him, Come out of the man, thou unclean spirit.

01:51.520 --> 01:54.580
And he asked him, What is thy name?

01:54.880 --> 02:00.160
And he answered, saying, My name is Legion, for we are many.

02:00.920 --> 02:07.200
And he besought him much, that he would not send him away out of the country.

02:07.200 --> 02:14.840
Now there was there, nigh unto the mountains, a great herd of swine feeding.

02:15.560 --> 02:22.300
And all the devils besought him, saying, Send us into the swine, that we may enter into them.

02:23.300 --> 02:25.940
And forthwith Jesus gave them leave.

02:26.420 --> 02:30.500
And the unclean spirits went out and entered into the swine,

02:30.860 --> 02:35.980
and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the sea.

02:35.980 --> 02:41.680
They were about two thousand, and were choked in the sea.

02:42.340 --> 02:49.340
And they that fed the swine fled, and told it in the city and in the country.

02:49.740 --> 02:54.340
And they went out to see what it was that was done.

02:55.340 --> 03:02.240
And they came to Jesus to see him that was possessed with the devil and the legion,

03:02.240 --> 03:06.340
sitting and clothed in his right mind.

03:06.860 --> 03:09.380
And they were afraid.

03:10.100 --> 03:19.660
And they that saw it told them how it befell to him that was possessed with the devil and also concerning the swine.

03:19.760 --> 03:23.360
And they began to pray him to depart out of their coast.

03:23.660 --> 03:31.160
And when he was come into the ship, he that had been possessed with the devil prayed him that he might be with him.

03:31.960 --> 03:36.040
Howbeit Jesus suffered him not, but saith unto him,

03:36.400 --> 03:45.500
Go home to thy friends, and tell them how great things the Lord hath done for thee, and hath had compassion on thee.

03:46.060 --> 03:54.080
And he departed and began to publish in Decapolis how great things Jesus had done for him.

03:54.080 --> 03:56.380
And all men did marvel.

03:56.900 --> 04:02.420
And when Jesus was passed over again by ship unto the other side,

04:02.900 --> 04:07.840
much people gathered unto him, and he was nigh unto the sea.

04:08.260 --> 04:14.100
And, behold, there cometh one of the rulers of the synagogue, Jarius by name.

04:14.460 --> 04:17.660
And when he saw him, he fell at his feet.

04:18.580 --> 04:24.580
And he besought him greatly, saying, My little daughter lieth at the point of death.

04:24.700 --> 04:32.540
I pray thee, come and lay thy hands on her, that she may be healed and she may live.

04:33.400 --> 04:38.840
And Jesus went with him, and much people followed him and thronged him.

04:38.840 --> 04:44.000
And a certain woman, which had an issue of blood twelve years,

04:44.320 --> 04:50.680
and had suffered many things of many physicians, and had spent all that she had,

04:51.000 --> 04:55.300
and was nothing bettered, but rather grew worse.

04:55.980 --> 05:03.020
When she had heard of Jesus, came in the press behind, and touched his garment.

05:03.020 --> 05:08.780
For she said, If I may touch but his clothes, I shall be whole.

05:09.180 --> 05:12.640
And straightway the fountain of her blood was dried up,

05:12.980 --> 05:17.520
and she felt in her body that she was healed of that plague.

05:18.400 --> 05:23.580
And Jesus, immediately knowing in himself that virtue had gone out of him,

05:24.040 --> 05:29.700
turned him about in the press, and said, Who touched my clothes?

05:29.700 --> 05:36.120
And his disciples said unto him, Thou seest the multitude thronging thee,

05:36.440 --> 05:38.580
and sayest thou who touched me?

05:39.120 --> 05:43.680
And he looked round about to see her that had done this thing.

05:44.140 --> 05:49.060
But the woman, fearing and trembling, knowing what was done in her,

05:49.260 --> 05:54.660
came and fell down before him, and told him all the truth.

05:54.660 --> 06:01.060
And he said unto her, Daughter, thy faith hath made thee whole.

06:01.380 --> 06:04.460
Go in peace, and be whole of thy plague.

06:05.340 --> 06:09.980
While he yet spake, there came, from the ruler of the synagogue's house,

06:10.220 --> 06:17.160
certain which said, Thy daughter is dead. Why troublest thou the master any further?

06:18.200 --> 06:21.140
As soon as Jesus heard the word that was spoken,

06:21.140 --> 06:27.160
he saith unto the ruler of the synagogue, Be not afraid, only believe.

06:28.420 --> 06:37.320
And he suffered no man to follow him save Peter and James and John the brother of James.

06:38.220 --> 06:41.900
And he cometh to the house of the ruler of the synagogue,

06:42.460 --> 06:47.720
and seeth the tumult and them that wept and wailed greatly.

06:47.720 --> 06:54.500
And when he was come in, he saith unto them, Why make ye this ado and weep?

06:54.620 --> 06:57.880
The damsel is not dead, but sleepeth.

06:58.300 --> 07:03.340
And they laughed him to scorn, but when he had put them all out,

07:04.080 --> 07:09.740
he taketh the father and the mother of the damsel and them that were with him,

07:09.980 --> 07:13.560
and entereth in where the damsel was lying.

07:13.560 --> 07:17.580
And he took the damsel by the hand and said unto her,

07:18.340 --> 07:25.060
Talitha cum I, which is being interpreted, Damsel, I say unto thee arise.

07:26.020 --> 07:32.880
And straightway the damsel arose and walked, for she was of the age of twelve years,

07:33.480 --> 07:37.740
and they were astonished with a great astonishment.

07:37.740 --> 07:42.240
And he charged them straightly that no man should know it,

07:42.420 --> 07:46.400
and commanded that something should be given her to eat.

07:47.680 --> 07:49.080
CHAPTER VI.

07:49.720 --> 07:55.900
And he went out from thence, and came into his own country, and his disciples follow him.

07:56.520 --> 08:01.400
And when the Sabbath day was come, he began to teach in the synagogue.

08:01.740 --> 08:04.900
And many hearing him were astonished, saying,

08:04.900 --> 08:11.280
From whence hath this man these things, and what wisdom is this which is given unto him,

08:11.540 --> 08:15.680
that even such mighty works are wrought by his hands?

08:16.360 --> 08:24.900
Is not this the carpenter, the son of Mary, the brother of James, and Osais, and Judah, and Simon,

08:25.220 --> 08:30.080
and are not his sisters here with us? And they were offended at him.

08:30.080 --> 08:37.420
But Jesus said unto them, A prophet is not without honor, but in his own country,

08:37.680 --> 08:41.980
and among his own kin, and in his own house.

08:42.720 --> 08:51.220
And he could there do no mighty work, save that he laid his hands upon a few sick folk and healed them.

08:51.620 --> 08:58.860
And he marveled because of their unbelief, and he went round about the village's teaching.

08:58.860 --> 09:06.560
And he called unto him the Twelve, and began to send them forth by two and two,

09:06.940 --> 09:14.260
and gave them power over unclean spirits, and commanded them that they should take nothing for their journey,

09:14.820 --> 09:26.300
save a staff only, no script, no bread, no money in their purse, but be shod with sandals, and not put on two coats.

09:26.300 --> 09:36.440
And he said unto them, In what place soever ye enter into, in house, there abide till ye depart from that place.

09:37.140 --> 09:45.620
And whosoever shall not receive you, nor hear you, when ye depart thence, shake off the dust under your feet,

09:45.620 --> 09:58.340
for a testimony against them, verily I say unto you, it shall be more tolerable for Sodom and Gomorrah in the day of judgment than for that city.

09:58.960 --> 10:09.840
And they went out and preached that men should repent, and they cast out many devils, and anointed with oil many that were sick and healed them.

10:09.840 --> 10:19.640
And King Herod heard of him, for his name was spread abroad, and he said that John the Baptist was risen from the dead,

10:20.000 --> 10:25.060
and therefore mighty works do show forth themselves in him.

10:25.420 --> 10:32.720
Others said that it is Elias, and others said that it is a prophet, or as one of the prophets.

10:32.720 --> 10:42.140
But when Herod heard thereof, he said, It is John whom I beheaded, he is risen from the dead.

10:42.460 --> 10:53.880
For Herod himself had sent forth, and laid hold upon John, and bound him in prison for Herodias' sake, his brother Phillips' wife.

10:53.880 --> 11:04.280
For he had married her. For John had said unto Herod, It is not lawful for thee to have thy brother's wife.

11:04.780 --> 11:12.380
Therefore Herodias had a quarrel against him, and would have him killed, but she could not.

11:12.380 --> 11:20.940
For Herod feared John, knowing that he was a just man, and unholy, and observed him.

11:21.220 --> 11:26.220
And when he heard him, he did many things, and heard him gladly.

11:27.080 --> 11:38.240
And when a convenient day was come, that Herod, on his birthday, made a supper to his lords, high captains, and chief estates of Galilee.

11:38.240 --> 11:50.980
And when the daughter of the said Herodias came in, and danced, and pleased Herod, and them that sat with him, the king said unto the damsel,

11:51.660 --> 12:04.700
Ask of me whatsoever thou wilt, and I will give it thee. And he sware unto her, Whatsoever thou shall ask of me, I will give it thee unto the half of my kingdom.

12:04.700 --> 12:16.160
And she went forth, and said unto her mother, What shall I ask? And she said, The head of John the Baptist.

12:17.060 --> 12:31.660
And she came in straightway with haste unto the king, and asked, saying, I will that thou give me, by and by, in a charger, the head of John the Baptist.

12:31.660 --> 12:43.900
And the king was exceeding sorry, yet for his oaths sake, and for their sakes which set with him, he would not reject her.

12:44.200 --> 12:49.400
And immediately the king sent an executioner, and commanded his head to be brought.

12:49.400 --> 13:00.940
And he went and beheaded him in the prison, and brought his head in a charger, and gave it to the damsel, and the damsel gave it to her mother.

13:01.840 --> 13:10.540
And when his disciples heard of it, they came and took up his corpse, and laid it in a tomb.

13:10.540 --> 13:20.760
And the apostles gathered themselves together unto Jesus, and told him all things, both what they had done, and what they had taught.

13:21.480 --> 13:37.480
And he said unto them, Come ye yourselves apart into a desert place, and rest awhile, for there are many coming and going, and they had no leisure so much as to eat.

13:37.480 --> 13:54.720
And they departed into a desert place by ship, privately. And the people saw them departing, and many knew him, and ran afoot thither out of all cities, and out went them, and came together unto him.

13:54.720 --> 14:06.820
And Jesus, when he came out, saw much people, and was moved with compassion toward them, because they were as sheep, not having a shepherd.

14:07.460 --> 14:20.400
And he began to teach them many things. And when the day was now far spent, his disciples came unto him, and said, This is a desert place, and now the time is far past.

14:20.400 --> 14:31.380
Send them away, that they may go into the country round about, and into the villages, and buy themselves bread, for they have nothing to eat.

14:31.380 --> 14:45.040
He answered and said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they say unto him, Shall we go and buy two hundred penny worth of food, and give them to eat?

14:45.040 --> 15:03.220
And he sayeth unto them, How many loaves have ye? Go and see. And when they knew, they say, Five and two fishes. And he commanded them to make all sit down by companies upon the green grass.

15:03.220 --> 15:21.020
And they sat down in ranks by hundreds and by fifties. And when he had taken the five loaves and the two fish, he looked up to heaven and blessed, and break the loaves, and gave them to his disciples to set before them.

15:21.020 --> 15:35.620
And the two fishes divided he among them all. And they did all eat and were filled. And they took up twelve baskets full of the fragments and of the fish.

15:35.620 --> 15:55.120
And they that did eat of the loaves were about five thousand men. And straightway he constrained his disciples to get into the ship and to go to the other side before unto Bethesda, while he sent away the people.

15:55.120 --> 16:09.600
And when he had sent them away, he departed into a mountain to pray. And when even was come, the ship was in the midst of the sea, and he alone on the land.

16:09.600 --> 16:24.400
And he saw them toiling and rowing, for the wind was contrary unto them. And about the fourth watch of the night he cometh unto them, walking upon the sea, and would have passed by them.

16:24.400 --> 16:41.660
But when they saw him walking upon the sea, they supposed it had been a spirit, and cried out. For they all saw him, and were troubled. And immediately he talked with them, and sayeth unto them, Be of good cheer, it is I, be not afraid.

16:41.660 --> 16:52.180
And when he went up unto them into the ship, and the wind ceased, they were sore amazed in themselves, beyond measure, and wondered.

16:52.180 --> 17:07.980
For they considered not the miracle of the loaves, for their heart was hardened. And when they had passed over, they came into the land of Geneseret, and drew to the shore.

17:07.980 --> 17:25.040
And when they were come out of the ship straightway, they knew him, and ran through that whole region round about, and began to carry about in bids those that were sick, where they heard he was.

17:25.040 --> 17:42.420
And whither soe'er he entered into villages, or cities, or country, they laid the sick in the streets, and besought him, that they might touch, if it were. But the border of his garment, and as many as touched him, were made whole.

17:56.840 --> 17:56.900
Thank you.

